00:26:11.920 --> 00:26:17.380
&gt;&gt; So how challenging was
it having a plot where like

00:26:17.380 --> 00:26:21.260
of course emotionally it would
matter the next day what they

00:26:21.260 --> 00:26:26.100
had done, but physically like
it didn't matter what they did,

00:26:26.100 --> 00:26:28.870
like you have so much room to
do anything you want there.

00:26:28.870 --> 00:26:30.170
So how did you do
that in your book?

00:26:30.170 --> 00:26:35.770
&gt;&gt; Marisha Pessl: You mean in
terms of having so much choice

00:26:35.770 --> 00:26:38.360
because of the infinity
nature f the time?

00:26:38.360 --> 00:26:39.660
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:26:39.660 --> 00:26:40.960
&gt;&gt; Marisha Pessl: That's
such a good question.

00:26:40.960 --> 00:26:46.990
So I had to limit myself
and I allowed the characters

00:26:46.990 --> 00:26:51.650
to tell me their limits
because I was bound

00:26:51.650 --> 00:26:54.680
by the nature of
these characters.

00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:59.420
And so characters kept
me to a grounded place

00:26:59.420 --> 00:27:02.860
as to what they were
going to do.

00:27:02.860 --> 00:27:11.170
Beatrice was going to actually
try to get everyone to vote,

00:27:11.170 --> 00:27:14.390
she was the responsible one.

00:27:14.390 --> 00:27:17.400
She was the one who
really wanted to try this.

00:27:17.400 --> 00:27:23.310
I won't go into all
of them, I don't want

00:27:23.310 --> 00:27:24.610
to give away too much.

00:27:24.610 --> 00:27:27.170
But I was bound by character.

00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:33.340
And I have found no matter what
character is what you always

00:27:33.340 --> 00:27:35.330
return to as a writer.

00:27:35.330 --> 00:27:40.260
Whether you're going, you're
writing a huge sprawling epic

00:27:40.260 --> 00:27:45.350
or a tiny little thing,
your characters are bound

00:27:45.350 --> 00:27:48.910
by their sheer nature of
mortality, their circumstance.

00:27:48.910 --> 00:27:53.780
It's really all about character
and that's the wonderful thing.

00:27:53.780 --> 00:27:58.020
And that really keeps
you as a writer grounded

00:27:58.020 --> 00:28:00.490
because you're writing
about people.

00:28:00.490 --> 00:28:03.930
That's why I don't think I've
ever, I won't limit myself,

00:28:03.930 --> 00:28:07.750
but to write about
aliens or something,

00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:13.750
then there would be no limits
and it would truly be scary.

00:28:13.750 --> 00:28:18.700
But people I can handle,
people have a corporality,

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:22.020
they have something
I can handle.

00:28:22.020 --> 00:28:27.220
So that's how I dealt
with that infinity.

